*<!--Apr 22--> A train '''[[2014 Katanga train derailment|derails]]''' in [[Katanga Province|Katanga]], Democratic Republic of the Congo, killing at least 48 people.
*<!--Apr 21--> More than 230 female students are declared missing after '''[[2014 Chibok kidnapping|a mass kidnapping]]'''  in [[Borno State]], Nigeria.
*<!--Apr 21--> At the '''[[2014 Boston Marathon|Boston Marathon]]''', American [[Meb Keflezighi]] wins the men's race and Kenyan [[Rita Jeptoo]] ''(pictured)'' wins the women's race.
*<!--Apr 18--> '''[[2014 Mount Everest avalanche|An avalanche]]''' on [[Mount Everest]] kills sixteen Nepalese guides.
*<!--Apr 18--> [[NASA]] ends the '''[[Lunar Atmosphere and Dust Environment Explorer|LADEE]]''' mission by intentionally crashing the spacecraft into the [[Moon]].
<!--End of blurbs-->
